&nbsp;
The question of security guarantees of Ukraine is particularly difficult: It is not clear who should provide them, so that they are considered reliable in the current circumstances. Trump has appointed American negotiating team leaders to resolve these and other issues: Secretary of State Marco Rubio, > Director of Cia John Ratcliffe>, National Security Counsellor Michael Waltz > and Special Envoy for the Middle East Steve Witkoff; > the latter, on the eve of Trump's call to Putin, on February 11 he went to Moscow to take the teacher Mark Vogel, released from a Russian prison in exchange for the release of the co-founder of cryptocurrency BTC-e, Alexander Vinnik.
